Packages 
Package Description
net.xuset.objectIO
ObjectIO is a framework with the purpose of simplifying the process of communicating to another computer and interpreting the received data.
net.xuset.objectIO.connections
Connections is the package which houses the how a message is sent.
net.xuset.objectIO.connections.sockets  
net.xuset.objectIO.connections.sockets.groupNet
GroupNet acts like a P2P infrastructure but is instead based on a TCP server-client model.
net.xuset.objectIO.connections.sockets.groupNet.client  
net.xuset.objectIO.connections.sockets.groupNet.server  
net.xuset.objectIO.connections.sockets.tcp  
net.xuset.objectIO.markupMsg
MarkupMsg is to objectIO as red blood cells are to the circulatory system.
net.xuset.objectIO.netObj
A NetObject is used for converting a MarkupMsg object into something meaningful.
net.xuset.objectIO.util
This package is for miscellaneous class like network pings, port scanners, and UDP broadcasting.
net.xuset.objectIO.util.broadcast  
net.xuset.objectIO.util.scanners
